We came out of town to visit, and went to this place because the reviews were good. When we walk in, we noticed a man counting some spare change to buy something. He ask for something to eat and pay in change. The lady at the counter made a remark about the homeless man.  I fell uncomfortable because we are not perfect but we try to be.  I don't laugh on other person mishap, troubles or life problems. I could be that person some day  . I don't know what turns life have for me . I look up , to heaven an pray the allways have mercy for me and those that don't have it like that. I won't recommend this place. Base on my principal.

The Beans have a weird taste for being a Spanish restaurant they should be perfect. That's like Starbucks having bad coffee.  The place is a grease trap. Filthy.  The back were the bathroom is has grease and dirt years old all over the place. The service is rude.  And non caring, gloves are never used, no hairnets. The servers wipe their nose , handle your money and then the food.  Gross I almost threw up. Buyer beware.

If I'm ever in Williamsburg, this is always my go-to spot to eat!! Good Latin food, cheap, and they accept credit cards which is a plus since I rarely carry cash. Forget all the chain restaurants or new hipster spots in Williamsburg.. go here instead!!

I love the chicken stew. I'm eating it now as I type or I'd write a longer review. It's cheap, and easily contains more than half a chicken, potatos carrots and an occasional green olive. And I get to practice my Spanish! I feel like family here.
The morcilla is off the damn hook. True NYC latin food for true NYers. We need more restaurants like this.

The place is a pig pen. I used the bathroom in the back of the kitchen and after dodging a mouse and almost falling due to the grease buildup.  And the stench of old grease and food is enough to know I will not be back to that pigstye.  Oh and the workers if you watch them since all they do is talk LOUD you see the spit going all over the place most of all the food. And the tall girl that works there if you watch her also she taste s' the food then licks her fingers clean right in front of everyone.  I wanted to throw up.  I need to check to make sure that A from the Dept.of health. Has to be phony or bought.  Don't say Joe didn't warn you.

Tons of food if you get their mini entrée, it's enough for two meals at $7. I got the ribs over rice with beans. I felt it was all a little too salty  and although some parts of my ribs were perfectly moist, a lot of it was dry and hard. My chicken empanadas were also pretty dry. It's okay for the price but I would go to the other spanish places in the area.
Old school Puerto Rican food!
The fried chicken tho

Food can be spot on, especially the rice and beans. Only complaint is the staff can be moody to non-Hispanic people, batting angry eyes, busting chops, procrastinating and sometimes even refusing service. Several friends have been getting sick from the food recently, too. I used to go here all the time, but find myself going less and less especially since it's been getting a bad rep recently.
